===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|龷|日|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=sun; day|tr=*sak}}. 

The semantic {{zh-l|*日}} indicates "past days". The phonetic top component originally depicted "rough/wrinkled" or "intertwined" textures; it was an independent character and the original ideogram for {{och-l|*腊|tr=*sak}} and {{och-l|*皵|tr=*sak}}.<ref>陳劍「說「昔」字並論「𡿧」形的真正來源」『饒宗頤國學院院刊』第八期 香港浸會大學饒宗頤國學院、2021年、1–46頁。</ref>

{{w|Shuowen}}: {{Han compound|仌|日|ls=ic}} – two pieces of flesh ({{zh-l|*仌}}) dried in the sun ({{zh-l|*日}}). Original form of {{zh-l|*腊}} (dried meat).

Similar but unrelated to [[展]], [[共]], and [[散]].

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*rV-jak||night, full 24-hour day, spend the night}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). {{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} relates this to {{och-l|夕}} and {{och-l|夜}}; however, see those two entries for more.

